Edition:
Quote: One of the biggest risks in high country shepherding is smothering. This can occur at difficult crossings, gateways or narrow gullies, where stock can stumble and go under. 'Smothering can be a problem with Merinos.' Other causes of smothering can be thoughtless shepherding or a dog that decided to ignore its stop whistle.
